<item>
            <title>[SPR-75] Error binding to int[]</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-75</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This follows on from a bug I previously reported in the forums (ClassCastException binding properties):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using SimpleFormController and a JavaBean-style command class which has an int[] defined within it. On my HTML form I have the following, the values of which should be bound to my int[]:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; name=&quot;deleteGroupIndexes&quot; value=&quot;0&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; name=&quot;deleteGroupIndexes&quot; value=&quot;1&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; name=&quot;deleteGroupIndexes&quot; value=&quot;2&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and so on ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I submit the form, binding works fine if more than one checkbox is selected, and my int[] contains the correct values. However if only one checkbox is selected, binding fails as it tries to bind it as an int instead of an int[].&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve modified BeanWrapperImpl (taken from CVS today) as shown below and this appears to fix the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
Yazybones&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;------------------&lt;br/&gt;
Replaces line 737 (the end of the if (newValue instanceof ..) else block)&lt;br/&gt;
------------------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;} else if (newValue instanceof Object) {&lt;br/&gt;
  Object result = Array.newInstance(componentType, 1) ;&lt;br/&gt;
  Object val = doTypeConversionIfNecessary(propertyName, propertyName + &quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot; + 0 + &amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;, null, newValue, componentType);&lt;br/&gt;
  Array.set(result, 0, val) ;&lt;br/&gt;
  return result;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
